        <!--?lit$592780969$-->
        <!--?lit$592780969$--><span class="touch"></span>
  </button></template><md-icon aria-hidden="true"><template shadowrootmode="open"><!----><slot></slot></template>keyboard_arrow_down</md-icon></md-icon-button><h2>Part 1 - Text Preprocessing</h2></div>
<p>Raw text is messy. Before any model can use it, we need to:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Lowercase</strong> everything (so "Good" and "good" are the same word)</li>
<li><strong>Remove HTML tags</strong> (IMDb reviews often contain <code>&lt;br /&gt;</code> etc.)</li>
<li><strong>Remove punctuation</strong> (most of it doesn't carry sentiment)</li>
<li><strong>Tokenise</strong> - split into individual words</li>
<li><strong>Remove stopwords</strong> - extremely common words ("the", "is", "a") that add noise</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p>💡 Notice: we are NOT removing all punctuation blindly. Negation words like "n't" matter!</p>
</blockquote></span></div>
